# Twedar Platform Architecture

## System Overview

Twedar is an AI-Enabled Smart Wedding Planning Platform. Monorepo with two workspaces:

```
twedar/
├── backend/          # Node.js + Express + TypeScript (port 5000)
├── frontend/         # Next.js 16 + React 19 + TypeScript (port 3000)
```

## Backend Architecture (Clean Architecture)

```
backend/src/
├── app.ts                  # Express app setup, route mounting
├── server.ts               # HTTP + Socket.IO server bootstrap
├── lib/
│   ├── auth.ts             # Better Auth instance (email/password, Google, Apple, Organization plugin, Admin plugin)
│   ├── db.ts               # PostgreSQL pool (Supabase PostgreSQL)
│   └── permissions.ts      # Organization-level access control statements
├── features/
│   ├── auth/               # Session validation, RBAC middleware, role types
│   ├── vendor/             # Profile CRUD, documents (Supabase storage), verification state machine, admin actions, public listing
│   ├── realtime/           # Socket.IO server, conversations, chat messages, notifications, presence
│   └── email/              # Nodemailer transporter, send-email use case
└── scripts/
    └── seed-admin.ts       # Admin user seeding
```

Each feature module follows:
```
features/<name>/
├── domain/           # Types, interfaces, business rules (no external deps)
├── use-cases/        # Application logic (depends only on domain)
├── infrastructure/   # DB repositories, external services, init-tables
└── presentation/     # Express routes, controllers, Socket handlers
```

**Dependency rule:** domain ← use-cases ← infrastructure/presentation. Inner layers never import outer layers.

## Frontend Architecture (Next.js App Router)

```
frontend/src/
├── app/
│   ├── (auth)/           # Login, register, verify-email, reset-password, social-callback
│   ├── (couple)/         # Dashboard, vendors discovery, vendor detail, messages
│   ├── (vendor)/         # Vendor dashboard, profile setup, messages
│   ├── (admin)/          # Admin dashboard, vendor moderation
│   ├── layout.tsx        # Root layout (fonts, metadata)
│   └── page.tsx          # Public marketing homepage
├── components/
│   ├── auth-guard.tsx    # Client-side role gate (wraps protected layouts)
│   ├── layouts/          # DashboardShell with sidebar nav
│   ├── realtime/         # ChatList, ChatWindow, NotificationDropdown, PresenceDot
│   ├── vendor/           # VendorProfileForm, DocumentUpload, LocationMapPicker
│   └── ui/              # Shared UI primitives
├── hooks/                # useSocket, useChat, useNotifications
├── services/             # API fetch wrappers (auth, vendor, public-vendor, admin-vendor)
├── lib/
│   ├── auth-client.ts    # Better Auth React client (signIn, signUp, useSession)
│   └── socket-client.ts  # Socket.IO singleton
└── types/                # Shared TS interfaces (auth, vendor, realtime)
```

## Database (PostgreSQL on Supabase)

Tables managed by this codebase:
- `vendor_profiles` — business data, geo, portfolio JSONB, price range, status workflow
- `vendor_documents` — FK to vendor_profiles, Supabase storage URLs
- `conversation` — two-participant unique pair
- `chat_message` — FK to conversation, content, sender, isRead
- `notification` — user-targeted, type, title, body, isRead

Tables managed by Better Auth (auto-migrated):
- `user`, `session`, `account`, `verification`, `organization`, `member`, `invitation`

## Authentication & Roles

| Role | Route Group | Access |
|------|------------|--------|
| couple | `(couple)/*` | Wedding planning, vendor discovery, chat, budget |
| vendor | `(vendor)/*` | Business profile, documents, chat, bookings |
| admin | `(admin)/*` | Vendor moderation, user management, analytics |

- Sessions: HTTP-only cookies (not JWT in localStorage)
- OAuth: Google + Apple (couples only)
- Organizations: Each vendor is a Better Auth Organization (owner + staff members)

## API Structure

All custom APIs under `/api/v1/`:
- `/api/v1/vendor/*` — authenticated vendor endpoints
- `/api/v1/admin/vendors/*` — admin-only vendor management
- `/api/v1/vendors/*` — public vendor discovery (no auth)
- `/api/v1/conversations/*` — authenticated chat REST
- `/api/v1/notifications/*` — authenticated notification REST

Better Auth endpoints: `/api/auth/*` (register, login, session, social, verify, reset)

Frontend proxies `/api/*` to backend via `next.config.ts` rewrites.

## Real-Time (Socket.IO)

- Server created alongside Express HTTP server
- Auth: session cookie validated on connection
- Rooms: `user:{userId}` for notifications, `conversation:{id}` for chat
- Events: `chat:send`, `chat:newMessage`, `chat:typing`, `chat:markRead`, `notification:new`, `presence:update`

## External Services

- **Supabase** — PostgreSQL database (via `pg.Pool` connection pooler) + Object storage for vendor documents
- **Nodemailer** — Transactional email (verification, reset, org invites)

